    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD represents a pinnacle of lightweight sports car engineering, featuring a numbers-matching 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powerplant exhibits exceptional compression across all rotor faces, paired with a crisp five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Its front-midship layout achieves a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, further enhanced by a factory-fresh four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and four-piston braking calipers. This specimen is mechanically flawless, with no vacuum leaks or thermal degradation of the engine harness. Preserved in showroom condition with a completely stock configuration and a pristine undercarriage, this FD is a rare find for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 44
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. Zero mechanical issues. Full service records included. Interior and exterior flawless.",
